{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7338fdea-5902-41a8-8468-9968251d3260","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Example usage:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\nNote: xUnit embeds the skip reason directly in `[Fact]`/`[Theory]` — there's no separate attribute. The other three use a standalone attribute alongside the test marker.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"46531ae0-6f04-407d-8123-40c57fcbf7b6","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly without tools.","outputTokens":321,"requestId":"5C46:2A473C:1A478D:20D2FA:69F54EFD"},"id":"ff60fe92-b167-4287-b8cb-5791a496b11d","timestamp":"2026-05-02T01:10:27.983Z","parentId":"ff1d10ad-1633-435a-acbb-7b522666f09d"}
